node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 13, 2021 tagging @tylerbossetti. May be an image of text that says 'Tyler Bossetti @tylerbossetti 3 mentality shifts that helped me take control of my life...'.

node.text:
Like most other people, @tylerbossetti didn't have a perfect upbringing but he didn't let that get in his way.

He got out of his toxic environment by becoming a door-to-door salesman and eventually transitioning into the mortgage industry, where he would learn the ins and outs of real estate.

He then used that knowledge to build a real estate fund that helps others invest in great real estate deals without doing any of the work.

If he can do it, anyone can.

Go follow him, he's putting out some great content @tylerbossetti 🔥

node.text:
Intoxicated manslaughter. Robberies. First degree murder. These are just some examples of the 102 high-stake cases I have been through and every single one of these cases have forced me to be the best, most persuasive version of myself. I have now devoted myself to teaching entrepreneurs and business owners how to become more credible and persuasive.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab Here are some practical tips to help you become a better speaker.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab Stop saying "umm" If you don't have anything important to add, don't add anything. There is nothing wrong with being silent.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 2. Be confident. If you speak with enough confidence, people will trust what you say anyway. Build your confidence through repetition.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 3 Be quick and concise. hundreds of Nobody wants to listen to filler words that aren't used intentionally. Just get to the point quicker.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 4. Use silence. Instead of using filler words or running in circles when you don't have anything to say, stay silent. Silence is powerful when paired with clear conversations.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 5. Appropriate presentation. It has nothing to do with speech, but dressing accordingly can help prove your point and deliver your message accurately. Don't overdo it, just look appropriate for the convo.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 6. Deliver emotion. if you can control what emotions your audience feels through your words, you can get them to do anything. Happiness, sadness, anger, any emotion works.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 12, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab learned all of this in 102 jury trials. If you want to see more tips about how to become a better speaker, follow me. My goal is to help everyone become a better speaker because it's an unfair advantage over others.'.
